## Fichier 2 — `compose/caddy/compose.yml`

Caddy doit être sur le réseau `ai` en plus de `frontend` pour accéder à open-webui, et ne plus monter les certs Tailscale (inutiles avec `tls internal`) :

```yaml
services:
  caddy:
    image: caddy:2.8.4
    container_name: caddy
    restart: unless-stopped
    ports:
      - "80:80"
      - "443:443"
      - "443:443/udp"
    env_file:
      - .env
    volumes:
      - ./Caddyfile:/etc/caddy/Caddyfile:ro
      - ${DATA:?err}/caddy/data:/data
      - ${DATA:?err}/caddy/config:/config
    networks:
      - frontend
      - ai
    security_opt:
      - no-new-privileges:true
    deploy:
      resources:
        limits:
          memory: 256M
          cpus: '0.5'
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD", "curl", "-f", "http://localhost:80"]
      interval: 30s
      timeout: 10s
      retries: 3
      start_period: 10s

networks:
  frontend:
    driver: bridge
    external: true
  ai:
    driver: bridge
    external: true
```

